40|$|The report {{contains}} three appendices {{from the}} Phase 1 final report. Appendix A contains <b>wet</b> <b>scrubber</b> {{sampling and analysis}} schedules, DBA/lime chemical analysis, and limestone forced oxidation chemical analysis. Appendix B consists of data on air toxic benchmarking baghouse conditions, ESP conditions, and <b>wet</b> <b>scrubber</b> conditions. Appendix C contains the quality assurance results. The primary objective of this project is to develop practical, cost-effective strategies for reducing the emissions of air toxics from coal-fired boilers. Phase 1 was aimed at providing a reliable test facility for conducting air toxic emissions control development work and is described more fully in the main report (OCDO [...] 96013945) ...|$|R
